                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>
                        <p>On fols. 1r, 2v, 23r, 66v, faceted initials in blue, green, or plum on rectangular backgrounds with concave sides and bevelled corners in the same colours; smaller initials plain red or blue. In the lower margin of fol. 1r on a delicately shaded blue background two standing putti support the Barbo arms, with a cross and cardinal’s hat above. Probably the dedication copy presented to <persName key="person_37985624" role="fmo">Cardinal Marco Barbo, patriarch of Aquileia</persName>, by Barozzi whilst bishop of Belluno, 1471–1487. (<ref target="https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/000468709">Pächt and Alexander</ref> ii. 560, pl. LII)</p>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
